Riders became stuck on a Disney California Adventure Park ride Thursday.

They were on Mickey's Fun Wheel 'for nearly two hours' while at the Anaheim, California amusement park,The Orange County Register reported. The park is part of Disneyland Resort. 

No one was injured in the incident, and the Ferris wheel was finally empty 'around 6pm,' the newspaper reported, which also said there were around 30 passengers.

Betsy Sanchez, a spokesperson for Disneyland Resort, told the newspaper 'All of our guests have been evacuated.'

